11/03/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Twelve young extremists have been charged in connection with the Thursday (March 8th) violence that marred students' demonstrations against the new government bill on higher educational reforms, according to prosecutors in Athens. 
According to the statement, another 41 protesters detained on Thursday may also face charges. 
A number of people were injured in the clashes between the protestors and police. 
(Kathimerini - 10/03/07; ANA-MPA, ERT - 09/03/07)
